#These gifs were created for a 64x32 board. There is no gurantees they will work elsewhere. They are called in renderers/game/game.py using paths such as "/home/USERNAME/animations/", and therefore would need to be moved to function
How to add gif playing utility:
cd rpi-rgb-led-matrix directory
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install libgraphicsmagick++-dev libwebp-dev -y
cd utils
make led-image-viewer

Example command to play a gif:
sudo ~/mlb-led-scoreboard/rpi-rgb-led-matrix/utils/led-image-viewer -t10 -D250 /home/USERNAME/fireworks/firework22lowert.gif --led-gpio-mapping="adafruit-hat" --led-rows=32 --led-cols=64 --led-brightness=80 --led-slowdown-gpio=4
